The paper discusses ethical concerns related to auditing commercial facial processing technology, which involves both computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV) aspects. The authors also discuss the potential harm to individuals and populations, which falls under the category of ethics and technology (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper highlights the importance of considering human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and the potential impact on society (cs.CY) when auditing facial recognition technology.
